<title>UK: Bradford &amp; Bingley prices 100 mln stg bond.</title>
<headline>Bradford &amp; Bingley prices 100 mln stg bond.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following subordinated step-up</p>
<p>callable bond has been priced by lead manager HSBC.</p>
<p> BORROWER   BRADFORD AND BINGLEY BUILDING SOCIETY</p>
<p> AMT    100 MLN STG   COUPON     8.0 PCT   MATURITY   *07.JUN.07</p>
<p> TYPE   STEP-UP	 ISS PRICE  99.937    PAY DATE   L21.MAY.97</p>
<p> FULL FEES  40 BP     REOFFER    99.937    SPREAD	+70 BP</p>
<p> MOODY	A3	  LISTING    LONDON    PAY FREQ    =</p>
<p> S&amp;P	  =	   DENOMS (K) 100	 SALE LIMITS US/UK</p>
<p> NEG PLG    NO	  CRS DEFLT  NO	  FORCE MAJ   IPMA (2)</p>
<p> GOV LAW    ENGLISH   HOME CTRY  BRITISH   TAX PROVS   STD</p>
<p> MGT/UND    20 BP     SELL CONC  20 BP     PRAECIPUUM  =</p>
<p>UNDERLYING GOVT BOND 7.0 PCT 2002 GILT</p>
<p> NOTES     L-LONG FIRST COUPON</p>
